        <article class="editorial-article" data-reveal>
            <p>
                The rivers of southwest Montana fish from late spring through early November, though the character of the fishing changes dramatically across those months. June brings the salmon fly hatch, one of the great spectacles in American fly fishing. July and August are prime dry-fly months. September and October are arguably the best of all&mdash;the crowds thin, the light goes golden, and the brown trout begin their fall run with an aggression that borders on recklessness.
            </p>
        </article>

